<paragraph blockId="7.[542,763,1094,1118]" box="[542,763,1094,1118]" pageId="7" pageNumber="2078">
(
<figureCitation box="[549,672,1094,1118]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[159,175,1589,1611]" captionTargetBox="[234,1040,166,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[231,1045,160,1570]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS 6–9. Male genital structures of Acrobelus nessimiani sp. nov. (6) Pygofer, anal tube, styles, connective, aedeagus and subgenital plates, dorsal view (one arm of the connective is broken). (7) Anterior portion of styles, valve, pygofer, subgenital plates and anal tube, ventral view. (8) Anterior portion of styles, pygofer, subgenital plate and anal tube, lateral view. (9) Aedeagus, paraphyses, dorsal apodemes and abdominal segment X, lateroventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676111/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="2078">figures 6–9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[687,755,1094,1118]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[154,170,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[156,1112,170,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[154,1112,170,1485]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS 10–16. Female genital structures of Acrobelus rakitovi sp. nov. and A. nessimiani sp. nov. (10, 11) A. rakitovi: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) A. nessimiani: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676113/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="2078">12–16</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[154,1111,1158,1732]" box="[194,686,1158,1182]" pageId="7" pageNumber="2078">Length of male 15.5 mm; female 16.5 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[154,1111,1158,1732]" box="[194,933,1190,1214]" pageId="7" pageNumber="2078">
External features of head and thorax as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ceotto &amp; Mejdalani &amp; Takiya, 2004" authorityName="Ceotto &amp; Mejdalani &amp; Takiya" authorityYear="2004" box="[707,830,1190,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acrobelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="2078" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rakitovi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[707,830,1190,1214]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="2078">A. rakitovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[840,933,1190,1214]" pageId="7" pageNumber="2078" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[154,1111,1158,1732]" lastBlockId="10.[159,1116,173,748]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="2081" pageId="7" pageNumber="2078">
Male genitalia with pygofer, in lateral view, moderately produced posteriorly; surface with numerous scattered microsetae mostly on ventral portion; posterior margin narrowed and subacute; pygofer without processes (
<figureCitation box="[860,945,1287,1311]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[159,175,1589,1611]" captionTargetBox="[234,1040,166,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[231,1045,160,1570]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS 6–9. Male genital structures of Acrobelus nessimiani sp. nov. (6) Pygofer, anal tube, styles, connective, aedeagus and subgenital plates, dorsal view (one arm of the connective is broken). (7) Anterior portion of styles, valve, pygofer, subgenital plates and anal tube, ventral view. (8) Anterior portion of styles, pygofer, subgenital plate and anal tube, lateral view. (9) Aedeagus, paraphyses, dorsal apodemes and abdominal segment X, lateroventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676111/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="2078">figure 8</figureCitation>
). Valve triangular; slightly convex on anterior margin and strongly convex on posterior margin; narrowed and fused with pygofer laterally (
<figureCitation box="[670,757,1352,1376]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[159,175,1589,1611]" captionTargetBox="[234,1040,166,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[231,1045,160,1570]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS 6–9. Male genital structures of Acrobelus nessimiani sp. nov. (6) Pygofer, anal tube, styles, connective, aedeagus and subgenital plates, dorsal view (one arm of the connective is broken). (7) Anterior portion of styles, valve, pygofer, subgenital plates and anal tube, ventral view. (8) Anterior portion of styles, pygofer, subgenital plate and anal tube, lateral view. (9) Aedeagus, paraphyses, dorsal apodemes and abdominal segment X, lateroventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676111/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="2078">figure 7</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plates, in ventral view, fused basally for very short distance; very elongate, extending well beyond pygofer apex; narrowly rounded apically and with emargination on inner margin of median third; surface with numerous scattered microsetae and many fusiform macrosetae densely distributed along most of inner margin and on apical one-third of outer margin (
<figureCitation box="[353,478,1514,1538]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[159,175,1589,1611]" captionTargetBox="[234,1040,166,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[231,1045,160,1570]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS 6–9. Male genital structures of Acrobelus nessimiani sp. nov. (6) Pygofer, anal tube, styles, connective, aedeagus and subgenital plates, dorsal view (one arm of the connective is broken). (7) Anterior portion of styles, valve, pygofer, subgenital plates and anal tube, ventral view. (8) Anterior portion of styles, pygofer, subgenital plate and anal tube, lateral view. (9) Aedeagus, paraphyses, dorsal apodemes and abdominal segment X, lateroventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676111/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="2078">figures 6–8</figureCitation>
). Styles, in dorsal view, extending well beyond apex of connective; with lobe on posterior one-third of outer margin; apical portion digitiform; apex narrow, rounded (
<figureCitation box="[552,639,1579,1603]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[159,175,1589,1611]" captionTargetBox="[234,1040,166,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[231,1045,160,1570]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS 6–9. Male genital structures of Acrobelus nessimiani sp. nov. (6) Pygofer, anal tube, styles, connective, aedeagus and subgenital plates, dorsal view (one arm of the connective is broken). (7) Anterior portion of styles, valve, pygofer, subgenital plates and anal tube, ventral view. (8) Anterior portion of styles, pygofer, subgenital plate and anal tube, lateral view. (9) Aedeagus, paraphyses, dorsal apodemes and abdominal segment X, lateroventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676111/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="2078">figure 6</figureCitation>
). Connective Y-shaped; stem longer than arms, its apex with lateral expansions (
<figureCitation box="[600,687,1611,1635]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[159,175,1589,1611]" captionTargetBox="[234,1040,166,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[231,1045,160,1570]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS 6–9. Male genital structures of Acrobelus nessimiani sp. nov. (6) Pygofer, anal tube, styles, connective, aedeagus and subgenital plates, dorsal view (one arm of the connective is broken). (7) Anterior portion of styles, valve, pygofer, subgenital plates and anal tube, ventral view. (8) Anterior portion of styles, pygofer, subgenital plate and anal tube, lateral view. (9) Aedeagus, paraphyses, dorsal apodemes and abdominal segment X, lateroventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676111/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="2078">figure 6</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus symmetrical; shaft short; curved dorsally in lateral view; with pair of small triangular dorsal processes on curvature; with very small microsetae on outer margin of curvature; apex of shaft slightly serrate; gonoduct opening on basal portion of shaft; dorsal apodemes large, semicircular (
<figureCitation box="[314,401,173,197]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[159,175,1589,1611]" captionTargetBox="[234,1040,166,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[231,1045,160,1570]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS 6–9. Male genital structures of Acrobelus nessimiani sp. nov. (6) Pygofer, anal tube, styles, connective, aedeagus and subgenital plates, dorsal view (one arm of the connective is broken). (7) Anterior portion of styles, valve, pygofer, subgenital plates and anal tube, ventral view. (8) Anterior portion of styles, pygofer, subgenital plate and anal tube, lateral view. (9) Aedeagus, paraphyses, dorsal apodemes and abdominal segment X, lateroventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676111/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figure 9</figureCitation>
). Paraphyses with rami very slender and short, not attaining one-half of aedeagal shaft (
<figureCitation box="[481,568,206,230]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[159,175,1589,1611]" captionTargetBox="[234,1040,166,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[231,1045,160,1570]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS 6–9. Male genital structures of Acrobelus nessimiani sp. nov. (6) Pygofer, anal tube, styles, connective, aedeagus and subgenital plates, dorsal view (one arm of the connective is broken). (7) Anterior portion of styles, valve, pygofer, subgenital plates and anal tube, ventral view. (8) Anterior portion of styles, pygofer, subgenital plate and anal tube, lateral view. (9) Aedeagus, paraphyses, dorsal apodemes and abdominal segment X, lateroventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676111/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figure 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
