<paragraph blockId="10.[159,1116,173,748]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[395,542,238,262]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[154,170,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[156,1112,170,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[154,1112,170,1485]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS 10–16. Female genital structures of Acrobelus rakitovi sp. nov. and A. nessimiani sp. nov. (10, 11) A. rakitovi: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) A. nessimiani: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676113/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figures 12–16</figureCitation>
) similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ceotto &amp; Mejdalani &amp; Takiya, 2004" authorityName="Ceotto &amp; Mejdalani &amp; Takiya" authorityYear="2004" box="[664,780,238,262]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acrobelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rakitovi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[664,780,238,262]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">A. rakitovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[785,872,238,262]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Sternite VII narrower than in the latter species and with median posterior lobe more strongly produced (
<figureCitation box="[166,267,302,326]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[154,170,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[156,1112,170,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[154,1112,170,1485]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS 10–16. Female genital structures of Acrobelus rakitovi sp. nov. and A. nessimiani sp. nov. (10, 11) A. rakitovi: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) A. nessimiani: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676113/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figure 12</figureCitation>
). Pygofer apex narrowed and subacute (
<figureCitation box="[729,828,302,326]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[154,170,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[156,1112,170,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[154,1112,170,1485]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS 10–16. Female genital structures of Acrobelus rakitovi sp. nov. and A. nessimiani sp. nov. (10, 11) A. rakitovi: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) A. nessimiani: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676113/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figure 13</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor with second valvulae, in lateral view, distinctly broadened beyond basal curvature, narrowing gradually toward acute apex (
<figureCitation box="[486,585,367,391]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[154,170,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[156,1112,170,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[154,1112,170,1485]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS 10–16. Female genital structures of Acrobelus rakitovi sp. nov. and A. nessimiani sp. nov. (10, 11) A. rakitovi: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) A. nessimiani: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676113/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figure 14</figureCitation>
); preapical prominence distinct (
<figureCitation box="[943,1042,367,391]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[154,170,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[156,1112,170,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[154,1112,170,1485]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS 10–16. Female genital structures of Acrobelus rakitovi sp. nov. and A. nessimiani sp. nov. (10, 11) A. rakitovi: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) A. nessimiani: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676113/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figure 15</figureCitation>
); teeth triangular, distributed from beginning of expanded portion to apex, those from expanded portion larger (
<figureCitation box="[446,596,432,456]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[154,170,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[156,1112,170,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[154,1112,170,1485]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS 10–16. Female genital structures of Acrobelus rakitovi sp. nov. and A. nessimiani sp. nov. (10, 11) A. rakitovi: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) A. nessimiani: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676113/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figures 14–16</figureCitation>
); denticles from preapical prominence to apex on ventral margin and on posterior portion of median surface of teeth (
<figureCitation box="[971,1070,465,489]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[154,170,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[156,1112,170,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[154,1112,170,1485]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS 10–16. Female genital structures of Acrobelus rakitovi sp. nov. and A. nessimiani sp. nov. (10, 11) A. rakitovi: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) A. nessimiani: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676113/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figure 15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[159,1116,173,748]" box="[199,1066,497,521]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">Colour mostly reddish brown; membrane of forewings translucent brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[159,1116,173,748]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">
<emphasis box="[199,328,529,553]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named in honour of Prof. Dr Jorge Luiz Nessimian (Departamento de Zoologia, Universidade Federal do 
<collectingRegion box="[934,1111,561,585]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[159,345,594,618]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
), whose dedication to entomology has inspired and stimulated the authors in the study of leafhoppers.
</paragraph>
